"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5410677-2024-04-12-nike-olympic-track-field-team-usa\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  The reveal of Nike's kits for Team USA's track and field Olympians has sparked controversy across social media as professional runners, Olympic hopefuls and fans zeroed in on the featured women's one-piece suit, which is unusually high-cut on the legs.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 20, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.945870618819923, \"rank\": 0.057226887416085524, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}, {\"begin\": 32, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9849996017351913, \"rank\": 0.015179955895993441, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is clearly a joke,\\\" Femita Ayanbeku, a two-time Paralympian wrote in a comment under an Instagram post of the uniforms.\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 350, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.966051417919546e-32, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am someone's mom, I can not be exposing myself in such ways.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where are the shorts?!\\\"\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  The men's design included in the first-look promo photo has shorts that hit the mannequin's mid thigh.\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A post shared by CITIUS MAG | Running + Track and Field News (@citiusmag)    During a Nike event unveiling the Team USA gear in Paris on Thursday, sprinter Sha'Carri Richardson and hurdler Anna Cockrell modeled other apparel options including a two-piece set and a bodysuit with compression shorts.\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.945870618819923, \"rank\": 0.057226887416085524, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}, {\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998144631, \"rank\": 1.853460489545355e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Cockrell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nike's chief innovation officer John Hoke said there are \\\"nearly 50 unique pieces across men's and women's and a dozen competition styles fine-tuned for specific events,\\\"per The New York Times.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.945870618819923, \"rank\": 0.057226887416085524, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}, {\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoke_County,_North_Carolina\", \"score\": 0.978058559651503, \"rank\": 0.015444015444015344, \"text\": \"Hoke\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoke_County,_North_Carolina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoke_County,_North_Carolina\"}, {\"begin\": 1068, \"end\": 1086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999999994411155, \"rank\": 4.209559843696488e-10, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's 2023 100m world champion Sha'Carri Richardson in the new Team USA Olympic team uniform by Nike.https://t.co/83xlsLbIGwpic.twitter.com/jCm72sgbCS  - CITIUS MAG (@CitiusMag)April 11, 2024    In response to the women's bodysuit included in the first-look promo photo, Grayson Murphy, a two-time world champion in mountain running said, \\\"that gusset is giving me anxiety\\\"  Likewise, two-time U.S. champion distance runner Lauren Fleshman ripped into the uniforms in a post on her Instagram account.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9849996017351913, \"rank\": 0.015179955895993441, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grayson_M._P._Murphy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grayson Murphy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grayson_M._P._Murphy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grayson_M._P._Murphy\"}, {\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999610731175087, \"rank\": 2.6986890417113433e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1514, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Fleshman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lauren Fleshman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Fleshman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Fleshman\"}, {\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.966051417919546e-32, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Professional athletes should be able to compete without dedicating brain space to constant pube vigilance or the mental gymnastics of having every vulnerable piece of your body on display.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's kits should be in service to performance, mentally and physically.\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If this outfit was truly beneficial to physical performance, men would wear it,\\\" Fleshman said.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The post continued, \\\"This is not an elite athletic kit for track and field.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a costume born of patriarchal forces that are no longer welcome or needed to get eyes on women's sports.\\\"\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes representing other countries also sounded off on the design.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Canadian hurdler and two-time Olympian Sage Watson wrote, \\\"Yeah, that's a no from me dog,\\\" and English long jumper Abigail Irozuru shared a photo of the uniforms to her Instagram story with the caption \\\"Was ANY female athlete consulted in this team kit?!?\\\"\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999777207452859, \"rank\": 2.2170632572667885e-05, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 2245, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999998553903, \"rank\": 1.444178340376436e-10, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2254, \"end\": 2265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sage_Watson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sage Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sage_Watson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sage_Watson\"}, {\"begin\": 2330, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abigail_Irozuru\", \"score\": 0.9999989479971267, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abigail Irozuru\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abigail_Irozuru\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abigail_Irozuru\"}, {\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.966051417919546e-32, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  The cut of the women's suit wasn't the only aspect of the design athletes took issue with.\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britton Wilson, a sprinter who holds the indoor American record for the 400-meter dash, asked \\\"why is the font comic sans\\\" under the Instagram post.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2579, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zack_Britton\", \"score\": 0.9953542854931043, \"rank\": 0.004667397895180999, \"text\": \"Britton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zack_Britton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zack_Britton\"}, {\"begin\": 2587, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilson_Sporting_Goods\", \"score\": 0.9991456151027993, \"rank\": 0.0006182336556418125, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilson_Sporting_Goods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilson_Sporting_Goods\"}, {\"begin\": 2627, \"end\": 2635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"